      "source": [
        "# 🧠 Jalon 2 : Modélisation Prédictive & Apprentissage (Squelette Étudiant)\n",
        "\n",
        "Dans ce notebook du **Jalon 2**, l'objectif est d'implémenter un pipeline complet d'apprentissage supervisé pour prédire une variable cible (`value`) à l'aide de Scikit-Learn. \n",
        "\n",
        "Vous devrez mettre en œuvre une stratégie de découpage train/test chronologique pour respecter la causalité temporelle.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 1. Préparation de l'environnement"
      ],
      "id": "a05316e9"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import sys\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score\n",
        "\n",
        "sys.path.append(os.path.abspath('..'))\n",
        "from src import data_clean as dc\n",
        "from src import utils_viz as uv\n",
        "\n",
        "uv.set_custom_style()\n",
        "print(\"Libraries de modélisation prêtes !\")"
      ],
      "id": "085eb5eb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Charger '../data/processed/cleaned_data_sample.csv'\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv('../data/processed/cleaned_data_sample.csv')\n",
        "df['timestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(df['timestamp'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Appliquer l'ingénierie de caractéristiques temporelles\n",
        "df_feat = dc.feature_engineering(df, 'timestamp')\n",
        "df_feat.head()"
      ],
      "id": "31c656ef",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### 2. Définition des variables et split chronologique\n",
        "\n",
        "**À faire par l'étudiant :**\n",
        "- Identifiez vos colonnes prédictives (`features`) et la colonne cible (`value`).\n",
        "- Séparez chronologiquement vos données en ensembles d'entraînement (`Train`) et de test (`Test`). N'utilisez pas de split aléatoire !"
      ],
      "id": "6345eb19"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Définissez la liste des variables prédictives (features) et de la cible (target)\n",
        "features = ['hour', 'dayofweek']\n",
        "target = 'value'\n",
        "\n",
        "# Split chronologique simple (ex: les 4 dernières lignes pour le Test)\n",
        "X_train = df_feat[features].iloc[:-4]\n",
        "y_train = df_feat[target].iloc[:-4]\n",
        "X_test = df_feat[features].iloc[-4:]\n",
        "y_test = df_feat[target].iloc[-4:]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Taille Train : {X_train.shape}, Taille Test : {X_test.shape}\")"
      ],
      "id": "a77691f0",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### 3. Entraînement du modèle de Forêt Aléatoire\n",
        "\n",
        "**À faire par l'étudiant :**\n",
        "- Instanciez et entraînez un modèle `RandomForestRegressor`.\n",
        "- Générez les prédictions `y_pred` sur l'ensemble de test."
      ],
      "id": "833f1207"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Instanciez et entraînez votre modèle RandomForestRegressor\n",
        "model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=10, random_state=42)\n",
        "model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Générez les prédictions y_pred\n",
        "y_pred = model.predict(X_test)\n",
        "print(\"Prédictions générées :\", y_pred)"
      ],
      "id": "9bd0c41e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### 4. Évaluation métrique\n",
        "\n",
        "**À faire par l'étudiant :**\n",
        "Calculez et affichez les scores d'évaluation requis :\n",
        "- **MAE** (Mean Absolute Error)\n",
        "- **RMSE** (Root Mean Squared Error)\n",
        "- **R²** (Coefficient de détermination)"
      ],
      "id": "021c6c4f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred))\n",
        "r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"MAE  : {mae:.3f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"RMSE : {rmse:.3f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"R²   : {r2:.3f}\")"
      ],
      "id": "4aa15578",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### 5. Importance des variables explicatives\n",
        "\n",
        "**À faire par l'étudiant :**\n",
        "Extrayez et affichez l'importance relative de chaque caractéristique prédictive."
      ],
      "id": "27036c83"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "importances = model.feature_importances_\n",
        "for feat, imp in zip(features, importances):\n",
        "    print(f\"Variable : {feat:12} | Importance : {imp:.4f}\")"
      ],
      "id": "fce11a55",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Modélisation Vision / Deep Learning (Analyse d'Images ou Signaux)\n",
        "*À rédiger par les étudiants : Expliquez l'intérêt de la brique de Deep Learning (images, signaux ou traitement de données structurées complexes) pour classifier ou enrichir vos prédictions. Détaillez l'architecture de votre réseau de neurones convolutif (CNN) conçu sous TensorFlow/Keras (conv, pooling, dense, dropout, activation) et commentez les courbes d'apprentissage obtenues.*\n",
        "\n",
        "[Détailler votre architecture CNN et analyse ici]\n",
        "\n",
        "### Travaux Pratiques de Vision par Ordinateur (CNN)"
      ],
      "id": "1e19796e"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Installation automatique des dépendances requises dans le noyau Jupyter actuel\n",
        "%pip install -r ../requirements.txt"
      ],
      "id": "7baa0acf",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# 📷 Jalon 2 : Brique de Vision par Ordinateur (CNN & TensorFlow) (Squelette Étudiant)\n",
        "\n",
        "Ce notebook est dédié à la brique d'analyse d'images du **Jalon 2**. L'objectif est de concevoir un Réseau de Neurones Convolutif (CNN) sous TensorFlow/Keras pour classifier des motifs géométriques simples (Classe 0: Cercle vs Classe 1: Multiples Rectangles).\n",
        "\n",
        "### 1. Préparation de l'environnement"
      ],
      "id": "27e7e7b4"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras import layers, models\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Version TensorFlow :\", tf.__version__)\n",
        "print(\"GPU Disponible :\", tf.config.list_physical_devices('GPU'))"
      ],
      "id": "7f174e5c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### 2. Génération du jeu d'images synthétiques\n",
        "Pour travailler de manière autonome sans importer de lourdes bases d'images externes, cette fonction utilitaire génère des images simulées en $64 \\times 64$ pixels de formes simples (Cercle vs Rectangles)."
      ],
      "id": "eecd0c2b"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def generate_dummy_images(num_samples=100):\n",
        "    images = np.zeros((num_samples, 64, 64, 3), dtype=np.float32)\n",
        "    labels = np.zeros(num_samples, dtype=np.int32)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    for i in range(num_samples):\n",
        "        label = np.random.choice([0, 1])\n",
        "        labels[i] = label\n",
        "        # Fond avec léger bruit\n",
        "        images[i, :, :, :] = 0.2 + np.random.normal(0, 0.01, (64, 64, 3))\n",
        "        \n",
        "        if label == 1:\n",
        "            # Classe 1 : Dessine plusieurs petits rectangles colorés\n",
        "            num_shapes = np.random.randint(5, 12)\n",
        "            for _ in range(num_shapes):\n",
        "                x = np.random.randint(5, 50)\n",
        "                y = np.random.randint(5, 50)\n",
        "                w = np.random.randint(6, 12)\n",
        "                h = np.random.randint(6, 12)\n",
        "                color = np.random.rand(3)\n",
        "                images[i, y:y+h, x:x+w, :] = color\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            # Classe 0 : Dessine un grand cercle central de couleur fixe\n",
        "            center_x, center_y = 32, 32\n",
        "            radius = 18\n",
        "            color = [0.8, 0.2, 0.2] # Rouge\n",
        "            for cy in range(64):\n",
        "                for cx in range(64):\n",
        "                    if (cx - center_x)**2 + (cy - center_y)**2 < radius**2:\n",
        "                        images[i, cy, cx, :] = color\n",
        "                        \n",
        "    images = np.clip(images, 0.0, 1.0)\n",
        "    return images, labels\n",
        "\n",
        "X_images, y_labels = generate_dummy_images(100)\n",
        "print(f\"Dataset d'images généré. Dimensions : {X_images.shape}\")"
      ],
      "id": "c983f567",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Visualisation de quelques exemples\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(10, 3))\n",
        "class_names = ['Cercle', 'Rectangles']\n",
        "for i, idx in enumerate([0, 1, 2, 3]):\n",
        "    axes[i].imshow(X_images[idx])\n",
        "    axes[i].set_title(class_names[y_labels[idx]])\n",
        "    axes[i].axis('off')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "d73e1dc2",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### 3. Split d'évaluation (Entraînement / Validation)\n",
        "\n",
        "**À faire par l'étudiant :**\n",
        "Divisez vos données d'images `X_images` et `y_labels` en $80\\%$ pour l'entraînement et $20\\%$ pour la validation."
      ],
      "id": "58478c64"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Divisez le dataset en ensembles d'entraînement et de validation\n",
        "split_idx = int(len(X_images) * 0.8)\n",
        "X_train, X_val = X_images[:split_idx], X_images[split_idx:]\n",
        "y_train, y_val = y_labels[:split_idx], y_labels[split_idx:]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Taille Train : {X_train.shape[0]} images, Taille Val : {X_val.shape[0]} images\")"
      ],
      "id": "d38e1d27",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### 4. Conception de l'architecture du CNN\n",
        "\n",
        "**À faire par l'étudiant :**\n",
        "Instanciez un réseau convolutif séquentiel Keras comprenant des couches `Conv2D`, `MaxPooling2D`, `Flatten`, `Dense` et un `Dropout` pour classifier nos deux formes géométriques."
      ],
      "id": "04841017"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Définissez l'architecture séquentielle de votre CNN\n",
        "model = models.Sequential([\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(16, (3, 3), activation='relu', input_shape=(64, 64, 3)),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "    layers.Flatten(),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(32, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.Dropout(0.2),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model.summary()"
      ],
      "id": "aa2f010b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### 5. Compilation et Entraînement\n",
        "\n",
        "**À faire par l'étudiant :**\n",
        "- Compilez le modèle avec l'optimiseur `'adam'` et la fonction de perte binaire.\n",
        "- Entraînez votre CNN sur environ 5 époques."
      ],
      "id": "bb38a49b"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Compilez le modèle\n",
        "model.compile(optimizer='adam',\n",
        "              loss='binary_crossentropy',\n",
        "              metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Entraînez le modèle\n",
        "history = model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=5, validation_data=(X_val, y_val))"
      ],
      "id": "0c6ec4bb",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
